name: Passo by Nook
address: Jl. By Pass Tanah Lot, Munggu, Kec. Mengwi, Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80351, Indonesia
review 1: I never knew this place before until my old friend asked me to meet up here. What a cute place. The portion was also quite big for me. The staff are nice. There's a swimming pool also. So u can enjoy ur meals & swim. And there are 3 friendly dogs, even better. Definitely wanna go back again.
review 2: I went to a quiet dinner here. The place was mostly empty and I could eat in peace within the tranquil surroundings. The chicken curry was great and I would recommend it.
review 3: Amazing hidden spot! Nice view on rice terrace, cool vibe with pool and good food ( fast service ) perfect for calm sunset
review 4: Passo By Nook is a great place to go if you want a comfortable setting with good coffee, friendly staff, and a complete menu. The restaurant is also kids friendly and has a swimming pool, so it is a great place to relax and unwind. Additionally, the internet is fast, making it a great place to do some work.¬†I can recommend Passo By Nook for anyone looking for a nice place to eat and relax in Bali.
review 5: This is my first time on this restaurant the service is good and I also like the place, good for relaxing and there is a pool there too. and I ordered tom yum because it was on their favorite menu list but after the food came I was very surprised because it couldn't be called tom yum at all, there was no taste in the tom yum soup üò¨üò¨

name: Warung Bamboo
address: Jl. By Pass Munggu, Tanah Lot, Munggu, Kec. Mengwi, Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80351, Indonesia
types: seafood_restaurant, barbecue_restaurant, vegetarian_restaurant, indonesian_restaurant, restaurant, food
review 1: Two different drivers on separate occasions took us to this location as it is a restaurant set up for tourists. There are swings and beautiful set ups to take photos of the rice paddy field while you wait for your meals. I was impressed by the grilled seafood they serve, so tasty. When your kids are fussy eaters like mine, this is a good place for the adults to enjoy local food and the kids to enjoy their usual food
review 2: Warung Bamboo is definitely a tourist trap. As a local living in Bali, I wouldn't recommend this restaurant. The food is overpriced with very small portions that don't justify the cost. The taste is mediocre at best. This will be the first and last time I visit this restaurant. There are far better and more reasonably priced options available elsewhere. Save your money and go somewhere else.
review 3: Great food, the place was spacious and had a nice look over the rice fields. Food portion was on the smaller side but overall tasty!
review 4: Thank you Augus ! You were super helpful and friendly ‚ò∫Ô∏è Food was fantastic! Enjoyable dinner !
review 5: Delicious food with reasonable rates and the staff here is very loving and well attended . Must visit while you are in Bali

name: What The Crab
address: Jl. By Pass Tanah Lot No.88, Munggu, Kec. Mengwi, Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80351, Indonesia
review 1:
We came here because my partner was craving sea food, and he's so satisfied now. The crab chowder was so tasty, even me who doesn't like sea food, I tried and I loved it, I could eat the whole soup myself. Then my partner took the 500g crab, and loved it. It was fun to see him fighting to get the meat inside.
I took the creamy chicken pasta, and the flavours were amazing.
The restaurant is in front of a rice field, it's so peaceful to eat while watching it.
The staff is very welcoming and kind.
Don't miss this place in Canggu, you'll not regret it !!
review 2: Overall, the atmosphere was lovely, the food was delicious, we ordered Mad Red Crab and Chilli Crab with level 2 spicy, it was a lil spicier than what we can handle, and we also have it with 500 grams crab, I wouldn‚Äôt recommend the smaller crab as its not very much meat inside. We have the fried mantou but it was overcooked and there are a lot of mosquitos in the area but they did provide us with the mosquito spray ;)
review 3:
I only went here to try and eat crab for the first time. For one time experience, this was great but I don‚Äôt see myself eating crab very often. The food is very tasty, the staff is very helpful and the atmosphere is beautiful.

The crab meat is very tasty. But in order to find the meat you need to ‚Äúfight‚Äù with the crab and break the shell. This can take time for inexperienced ones. It took me one almost one hour to break the crab and finish the meat.

I recommend order something else together with the crab. A soup for example. Everything tastes good here.

For those curious, the crab meat tastes like shrimps, maybe a bit more sweet than shrimps.

Enjoy the experience! üôÇ
review 4: Really delicious crab! I loved the Indonesian red and my husband really liked the Singapore Chili crab. It is better than some of the crab we had in Singapore ! Fried buns were a highlight too. Staff were really friendly and the view was great. Unfortunately forgot to take photos of the crab because it looked so good and we dug right in
review 5: Wow! Just woooooow! I came here alone because I was craving for ü¶Ä and I live in the neighborhood, I always see this place and wanted to try.. the crab was super fresh, the sauce is amazing, it‚Äôs sweet & spicy!! I regret I ordered only 1! I definitely coming back!!! Great job!!!! Thank youuuu

name: Kisah Rempah - Indonesian Restaurant Canggu Pererenan
address: Jl. Babadan, Munggu, Kec. Mengwi, Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80351, Indonesia
review 1: Beautiful restaurant with arched windows, a terrace and a rooftop in a calm area of Canggu. The sate, rendang and eggplant balado were our favourites. Coconuts are chilled (instead of room temp like many other places). Funny dog called Blackie who was super friendly and loved a pat. Will definitely swing by next time we‚Äôre in Bali! Thanks Claudia üòä
review 2: I won't be exaggerating if I call this the best place in Bali. Located in Canguu area, is run by a family and everyone is so nice and helpful. I had chicken steak and ice tea which was just amazing. The interiors of the cafe itself remained of Mediterranean theme restaurants and architecture which is very soothing.
review 3:
This restaurant is a true hidden gem! Superb food, awesome prices and incredible sunset views of the rice fields all around‚Ä¶just wow! Also the staff there is super super nice and very attentive.

We ate sweet and sour chicken, beef rendang and cap cay‚Ä¶ it was one of the best 3 dishes we had for a long long time. I highly recommend anyone to come here and try their food, you will not regret it!
review 4: BEST Chiken sate in Bali!! Everything is delicious, chinese kongpao chicken is also authentic. Highly recommend
review 5: Nice place to eat. The food and drinks were delicious and at a really nice price. The staff were so lovely (including the dog of course!). Didn't get the name of our waitress but she's was very sweet. Would recommend to come here!

name: Japa Guesthouse
address: Unnamed Road, Munggu, Kec. Mengwi, Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80351, Indonesia
review 1:
Perfect, clean, quite place.

Coffee is really good compare to many other places. Price are the best . Friendly staff. Worth to come back again.
review 2: Loved this place. Quiet, chill, clean, comfortable rooms and very kind staff. The restaurant is also nice!
review 3: The owner and staff are incredibly friendly, offering a great selection of food in their cosy cafe. While the room could use some improvement in terms of cleanliness and maintenance, everything else makes it an ideal place for a 5-night stay!
review 4: Great place to stay. The staff is very friendly and hard-working. They make sure the rooms are always clean, the grass is always cut and the pool is always inviting. The rooms are comfortable and spacious. Highly recommended!
review 5:
Nothing to complaints about
Everything was perfect
Definitely gonna come back and will recommend this place to my colleagues and friends

name: Bruann Residence
address: 94CG+V8W, Munggu, Mengwi, Badung Regency, Bali 80351, Indonesia
review 1: This villa offers an exceptional experience with its tranquil surroundings, tasteful decor, and stylish ambiance. The serene atmosphere makes it an ideal retreat, and the attention to detail in the decoration adds a touch of luxury to the stay. Highly recommended for those seeking a peaceful and aesthetically pleasing getaway.
review 2: I loved everything about this place. Great value and a gorgeous villa to get away from the hectic Canggu noise and traffic. The staff were excellent and super accommodating as well. For those bugs and insect comments, geez - you‚Äôre in the tropics! Live a little üòâ
review 3: Bruann Residence Villa 2 was simply amazing. High value for money. We loved everything about our stay. Gede was always in touch via whatsapp should we needed something. He also arranged a scooter for us. We will definitely stay here again and highly recommend this place.
review 4:
After staying in the heart Canggu we decided to find a place without traffic and all that noise‚Ä¶ it is getting so annoying there. We then found BruAnn residence! I would like to tell you guys, it is the gem of Villas in Bali! New, quiet, peaceful, and an absolutely amazing view! We watched the sunsets every day from our balcony and it was our favorite memories. The Villa staff are so friendly and responsible! Very good communication!
Overall, we ended up wanting to extend our stay, but the villa was booked for months in advance. So I booked for later dates now! I suggest to anyone who would like to stay here to also try and book now because I am sure it will be gone soon! üôèüèª
review 5: Putu and his staff were amazing, the best hospitality! The villa was spectacular and the views are breathtaking. I highly recommend and will be back soon!

name: Babi Guling Men Janji 2 Cabang Luwus - Baturiti
address: 94CJ+4HG, Munggu, Mengwi, Badung Regency, Bali 80351, Indonesia
review 1:
On a mission to eat all babi guling and this place prob tops out ATM. It is kinda out of the way, thus you don't get crazy crowds, only saw locals when I was there.

Got two plates of pisah but I think this place prob is tad spicier, but all in all, they have well balanced everything. Good chili, good portion of rice, meat that is not too dry, good meat floss, good keropok, only thing is the thick crispy skin can be less fatty for more crisp. Oh the soup is so good and have some small portion of meat on it which was delicious.

That bike ride here, worth it and will do again
review 2: Delicious :) reasonably priced, served with red rice, & beef soup. More of a local restaurant than for foreigners. But I like it that way :) The Babi guling is simple, no frills with pieces of crunchy thick rind, spicy side dishes and of course the delicious crispy Babi guling. The soup has a real kick to it. Recommend a cold glass of Teh Botol to match. An extra bonus is the rice field view! Would recommend and come again üëç
review 3:
I paid IDR 25K for this fantastic babi guling breakfast

so yummy and fresh !
review 4:
One of my favourite babi guling. The portion is super big with afordable price IDR 20.000 include a plate of meat and veggies, soup and rice.
All the babi guling and the condiment meal tastes good and spicy.
Very worth to try
review 5: Accidentally pass this place, and saw a lot of people eat here. Food turned out great, portions are normal, cheaper than other babgul place. I can say this place serve the best soup. For me this place is better than other 'famous' babi guling restaurant.

name: Bali Polo Club
address: Jalan Pantai Lima, Pererenan, Kec. Mengwi, Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80361, Indonesia
review 1:
Best Beach Gallop ever!!
I took "Beach Freedom Experience" package (disclaimer : only for experience riders) I can walk, trot, canter and even gallop by the beach!!
Coach Angkin gave super clear instruction so I feel safe and comfortable with Pearl Angel (the horse).
Coach and groomers also very helpful to took some photos and videos for me
review 2: The most unic and thrilling experience was visiting Bali Polo Club in Canggu. The sunrise rides on the beach are must try. Anybody can go even if no experience. When visiting equestrian clubs I look at horses‚Äô condition and this horses are in amazing health and shape. I could notice the amount of care they get. The stuff are very professional, skilled and will help you with pictures.:p
review 3: My first ever Sunset Horse Riding! I really enjoyed the horse ride. In fact, it was the highlight of my tripüëå. Everything was perfect, the incredible views, the horses, and excellent guide (very patient and understanding). Would absolutely recommend it to anyone who is looking for a unique experience in Baliüòä
review 4: My husband and I came to Bali on our honeymoon and this experience really was one of the highlights of our trip! We had a really enjoyable, lengthy ride with beautiful horses. We felt secure with the horses (first time riders) as there were attendants walking with us the whole time. Strolling through the beautiful rice fields and on the gorgeous Bali beach left us wanting to come back again for more!
review 5:
Bali Polo Club
its my second home my playground too.
I become their first patron since the very beginning of their soft opening, i train from 0 and now i can say i can stick and ball with horses.
It was a beautiful and soulfull journey for me,
i am a proud patron, they really take a good care of their hoseses, i can say it a must experience for people who wants to do something unique in Bali.

review 1: Amazing value for money! We were looking for a restaurant at 10:30 pm and were so happy to find this place. The staff is super friendly, dishes are affordable and really tasty! Plus, you get a view over the rice fields. A portion of sushi is only ‚Ç¨3. One small thing - it‚Äôd be better if they made it clearer that they‚Äôre open. There‚Äôs a sign saying they are, but it‚Äôs on the side and not very visible. It‚Äôs away from the touristy center. Would definitely recommend!
review 2:
I come here at least once a week.
My favorite place for sashimi, miso soup and buritos...
Always super fresh quality and quick service and very very fair priced.
No nonsense good quality food ü§©
review 3: The Food is fresh. Love everything,  especially the grilled eggplant. Fish also amazing
review 4: Simple setting in Airy space. We were there for lunch... light breeze... nice rice paddies view.  Toilet door lock did not work properly.
review 5: I've been there twice, and the first time the food was decent, but this last time, we barely ate not finished our food, and we ordered like 6 different dishes. Atmosphere is dead with no energy,  arrived and staff were playing cards , they look bored,  the local music has loud commercials, there's no attentiveness, care or knowledge of service dressed in basic streetwear. With no guests how can the food be fresh,  there's no love and no care and no business...I won't go back

review 1: Awesome reggae bar.  Local place but cool with Bule and tourists.  Popular place for tourist girls to meet local surfer guys with cool hair.  Super friendly.  Great music.
review 2: Nice place to chill out, grab your beer...listen live music, around pantai lima street
review 3: I hate to do this but I have been living in this area for the past 2 years peacefully. We moved here for the quiet vibes and have made great friends in the area who all feel the same way as us. This new bar has no sense of respect for the surrounding people living in the area. The music is so loud it feels as if the band is playing in our bedroom. Please owner if you read this sort it out, it's not fair on us.
review 4: Good place to watch live music performance and of course drink, eat, and chill with your friends üçªü§ó
review 5:
How & why would a loud music bar open on a zoned peaceful residential street surrounded by just ricefields, villas and even a breathwork shala?

Design is basic, limited menu, average music and zero party environment or atmosphere on this street. Save ur money for a local bar that respects their community and is in a more fun suitable area zoned for entertainment and night life! Plenty great spots on Batu bolong , Jalan Raya even Pererenan to bother driving out of the way for!

name: Babi Guling Sudirasa
address: Jl. By Pass Tanah Lot, Munggu, Kec. Mengwi, Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80351, Indonesia
review 1: Nasi campur babi guling ran me $2 or about 30k IDR. I'm not sure why people are saying that they charge tourists more, I definitely don't look Indonesian lol. Stopped by on the way back from tanah lot. Not bad at all!
review 2: I got the nasi babi guling special cause what else are you going to get at a place with an expertise in babi guling. I‚Äôve been in Bali about a month and when I tell you this was the best meal I‚Äôve had- nothing else even came close! Seriously the flavors were unreal. Everything worked together the long beans, the kefir lime, the pork cooked more ways than I could count and the broth of the soup was really fantastic. I could have sat down and drank a whole liter of that soup. I guess if they see that you‚Äôre a westerner they assume you don‚Äôt want any sambal but I‚Äôm glad I asked for it because it was the mot perfectly balanced sambal I‚Äôve tried (and my ex is indo haha). And all that for 50k for the special large portion. Even with a western appetite I am stuffed. Glad I decided to drop in as I was driving by. Definitely make a trip if you have a craving. It almost felt like robbery to get so much good food for so little money!
review 3: Okay they charge 70k for this (6pieces) TOURISTS JUST DONT COME HERE
review 4: If you want to try thw local.Balinese with spicy food.. this is the place. The crisp.of thw pork i really good.
review 5: TOO EXPENSIVE. Rp65.000 for a portion of Nasi Babi Guling Spesial which is not so special. Flies everywhere. Not recommended.
